<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIFE IN LOS ANGELES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The following is a selection of subjects on the front page of today's Metro 
Section (Oct. 24): 
</P>
<P>
 -- Early release of 325,644 accused or convicted felons due to overcrowded 
jails. 
</P>
<P>
 -- 64 Glendale houses damaged or destroyed, due to "overtaxed" firefighters. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Extremely questionable financial shenanigans between Mayor Tom Bradley and 
his greedy friend, Juanita St. John. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Money-skimming trial of seven Los Angeles County sheriff's narcotics 
officers. 
</P>
<P>
I didn't have the guts to go past the first page. Does anyone else have the 
feeling that our city is out of control? 
</P>
<P>
JOHN DEGATINA, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
