<HEADLINE>
<P>
KHALIDI ON ISRAEL AND PALESTINIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If Khalidi is a teacher of modern Middle Eastern history, he conveniently 
forgets about Israel's peace treaty with Egypt. Egypt got the entire Sinai back 
with its oil resources and peace with Israel as well. 
</P>
<P>
Khalidi mentions Resolution 242, which calls "for an end to the state of war." 
Why don't Khalidi and the other Arab intellectuals suggest to the other Arab 
nations that peace treaties with Israel probably would lead to a withdrawal 
from occupied territories? 
</P>
<P>
Khalidi knows, of course, that Dennis Prager (Commentary, Oct. 12) is correct 
in stating that the Arabs will settle for nothing less than the destruction of 
Israel. 
</P>
<P>
Articles, such as Khalidi's, are only rhetoric that will not convince 
intelligent, unbiased readers. 
</P>
<P>
MARTIN J. WEISMAN, Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
