<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
THOUSAND OAKS ROLLS TO 5TH LEAGUE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Led by Kaili Kimura with a team-high eight kills, Thousand Oaks High clinched 
the Marmonte League girls' volleyball title with a 15-4, 15-1, 15-11 victory 
over host Camarillo on Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
Erikka Gulbranson had six kills and eight digs for the Lancers, who have won or 
shared five league titles in Ron Beick's five years as coach. 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks (16-3, 11-0 in league play) is ranked fifth in the Southern 
Section 5-A Division poll and 10th in the state. 
</P>
<P>
In other volleyball matches: 
</P>
<P>
Royal d. Agoura 15-9, 15-4, 15-11 -- Wende Brown had 16 kills and Jennifer 
Hamilton added 13 for Royal (13-2, 11-2), which secured second place in the 
Marmonte standings with the win at home. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame d. Alemany, 16-14, 15-6, 15-4 -- Mary Strong had 11 kills and 
Phyliss Francis added 10 for Notre Dame (12-3, 8-1) in a Mission League match 
at Alemany. 
</P>
<P>
The victory clinched at least a share of the league title for Notre Dame, 
ranked No. 2 in the Southern Section 4-A. 
</P>
<P>
El Camino Real d. Cleveland, 15-5, 15-7, 15-7 -- Jennifer Dinaberg had eight 
kills and Jessica Dinaberg added seven for El Camino Real (12-0, 9-0) in a 
Northwest Valley Conference match at Cleveland. 
</P>
<P>
L. A. Baptist d. Marshall Fundamental, 15-6, 15-1, 15-7 -- Monica Davis had 
eight kills for L. A. Baptist (14-1, 8-1) in an Alpha League match at home. 
</P>
<P>
Sarah Rameson added six kills for L. A. Baptist, ranked No. 5 in the Southern 
Section 1-A. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 7, Oxnard 0 -- Sergio Pizano scored two goals to lead the Raiders 
(14-0, 9-0) to a Western State Conference win at home. 
</P>
<P>
Tony Blat, Shaun Christensen, Billy Kranz, Richie Rungaitis and Jeff Spach each 
scored once for Moorpark, which is ranked sixth in the state. 
</P>
<P>
Angelo Maccano and Mike Zemansky combined on the shutout in goal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
