<HEADLINE>
<P>
KENNEDY APPOINTS CO-COACHES FOR GIRLS' BASKETBALL PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Donis Bailey and Bob Stevens will coach the Kennedy High girls' basketball 
program this year, replacing Toya Holiday. 
</P>
<P>
Bailey and Stevens were assistants to Craig Raub, who coached the Golden 
Cougars from 1978-87. Under Raub, the school won three City Section 4-A 
Division titles. 
</P>
<P>
Holiday, who recently gave birth to her second child, resigned to concentrate 
on her family and teaching career at Frost Junior High. Holiday, a former 
Kennedy standout, led the Golden Cougars to three North Valley League titles in 
three years as coach. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy currently has a 130-game winning streak in league play, the longest in 
the state. 
</P>
