<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two-Year T-Bill Rates Fall: Yields on two-year Treasury notes fell in Tuesday's 
auction to the lowest level since December. 
</P>
<P>
The average yield was 7.84%, down from 8.18% at the last auction Sept. 25. It 
was the lowest rate since two-year notes averaged 7.71% on Dec. 19, 1989. The 
notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 7.75%, with each $10,000 in face 
value selling for $9,983.60. 
</P>
