<HEADLINE>
<P>
WILLIAM FRENCH SMITH RITES SET FOR FRIDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A funeral service for former U.S. Atty. Gen. William French Smith, who died 
Monday at the Kenneth Norris Jr. 
</P>
<P>
Cancer Hospital at County-USC Medical Center, will be held Friday at 11 a.m. at 
the Community Church of San Marino. 
</P>
<P>
Smith, a UCLA and Harvard Law School graduate and a senior partner of the 
Gibson Dunn &amp; Crutcher law firm, was 73. He was a longtime supporter of 
former President Ronald Reagan, who named him attorney general in 1981. 
</P>
<P>
In lieu of flowers, the family is asking that contributions be made to the 
William French Smith Memorial Fund at the hospital. 
</P>
