<TEXT>
<P>
A 15-year-old hunter from Dunsmuir in Northern California has claimed the 
California state record for a black bear, 675 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Jones, bear hunting for the first time, shot the animal once in the head 
from 35 feet with a .357 magnum handgun as hounds owned by his father, Keith 
Jones, held the bear at bay near Lake McCloud Oct. 23. 
</P>
<P>
The bear measured 86 inches from the tip of its nose to its tail and had a 
72-inch girth. Its age was estimated at 20. 
</P>
