<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP VOLLEYBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SEA KINGS WIN TITLE IN SEA VIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Corona del Mar High School clinched its third consecutive Sea View League 
girls' volleyball title Tuesday night by sweeping University, 15-4, 15-10, 
15-4, at Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
The Sea Kings (19-1, 9-0) won their 17th consecutive match and are virtually 
assured of being the top-seeded team for the Southern Section 5-A tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Tournament pairings will be announced Monday, with first-round games starting 
Nov. 8. 
</P>
<P>
"Even if we had lost tonight and Thursday, I still think we would be the 
top-seeded team," said Dale Flickinger, Corona del Mar's interim coach. 
</P>
<P>
Middle blocker Lara Carlsen had seven kills and outside hitter Tracy Schriber 
added five to lead a balanced Corona del Mar attack. 
</P>
<P>
Outside hitter Lynn Randall added five kills and three aces for the Sea Kings, 
who finish the regular season Thursday night against league rival Newport 
Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
Randall served her three aces in the first game as Corona del Mar broke a 3-3 
tie with a 12-1 run. 
</P>
<P>
Flickinger substituted freely throughout the third game as Corona del Mar built 
an 8-2 lead. University got no closer than five points. 
</P>
<P>
Lemia Astarabadi had six kills and Holiday Molway had five to lead University 
(8-7, 2-7). MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
