<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TOP-SEEDED PLAYERS BEATEN IN THE EMPIRE LEAGUE FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Upsets in the singles and doubles finals marked the Empire League tennis 
individual championships Tuesday at Old Ranch Tennis Club in Seal Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos High senior Laura Brun, the No. 2-seeded player, won the singles 
title with a 7-6, 6-3 victory over top-seeded Traci Botha of El Dorado. 
</P>
<P>
In doubles, El Dorado's Tamie Hanson and Tempa Rainey -- the third-seeded team 
-- rallied to defeat Los Alamitos' Stefanie Springosky and Meredith Valt, the 
top-seeded team, 1-6, 6-3, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Brun's victory avenged her only two losses this season. She had a 28-2 record, 
the losses coming at the hands of Botha, the league's player of the year. Botha 
was 29-1 in league, losing only to Katella's Debbie Vonusa. 
</P>
<P>
Brun used her hard serve and excellent passing shots to wear down Botha, who 
made numerous unforced errors. It was Brun's first victory over Botha in seven 
attempts. 
</P>
<P>
In doubles competition, Hanson and Rainey entered the match as underdogs to the 
league's doubles team of the year, and in the early going it looked as if 
Springosky and Valt were on their way to another victory. 
</P>
<P>
But aggressive net play by the winners, particularly in the third set, turned 
the match around. 
</P>
<P>
"We didn't beat them once (during the season) but it doesn't matter. We beat 
them here," Rainey said. 
</P>
<P>
Third place in the singles finals went to Los Alamitos sophomore Susan 
Huberman. FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
