MORNING REPORT: RADIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Games People Play: A contest on KEZY-FM in which listeners guess whether the 
owner of a convenience store is American- or foreign-born has some members of 
Orange County's Human Relations Commission charging racism, but station 
officials said Tuesday they have no plans to take the contest off the air. 
Morning drive-time deejay Chris Little began playing "Foreign or Domestic" last 
month and calls it "a benign little game that's designed to be entertaining." 
CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
