<HEADLINE>
<P>
HAUNTING EVENTS IN NEIGHBORHOOD; 
</P>
<P>
HALLOWEEN: GHOULISH MUSIC AND CARNIVALS, ALONG WITH A BITE-SIZED VERSION OF 
'THE PHANTOM OF THE OPERA,' ARE AMONG THE LOCAL OFFERINGS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KENNETH WILLIAMS, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In case you're still having trouble figuring out how to scare up some Halloween 
fun and chills, here's a last-minute list of community carnivals, haunted 
houses, spooky plays and monster mashes. Read on, if you dare. . . . 
</P>
<P>
A Children's Halloween Party is being held from 3 to 7 p.m. at the Corona del 
Mar Library, 420 Marigold Ave., Corona del Mar. Admission is free. Call (714) 
644-3135. 
</P>
<P>
Halloween carnivals sponsored by the city of Santa Ana begin at 5:30 p.m. at El 
Salvador Park, 1825 W. Civic Center Drive; Jerome Park, 726 S. Center Drive; 
and Memorial Park, 2101 S. Flower St., Santa Ana. Admission: free. Game and 
activity prices vary. Call (714) 549-6887. 
</P>
<P>
A Halloween carnival sponsored by the city of Tustin runs from 6 to 9 p.m. at 
the Tustin Area Senior Center, 200 S. C St., Tustin. Admission: free. Game and 
activity prices vary. Information: (714) 544-8890. 
</P>
<P>
A bite-sized version of "The Phantom of the Opera" is being staged in a garage 
at 5803 Holmby Court in Cypress. The 20-minute show begins at 6 p.m. and will 
be repeated until about 9:15. Admission: free. Call (714) 826-6911. 
</P>
<P>
A Halloween Skate Party takes place from 6:30 to 8:30 p.m. at the Holiday Skate 
Center, 175 N. Wayfield, Orange. Admission: $2.75, includes skate rental. Call 
(714) 997-5515. 
</P>
<P>
The ninth annual "Haunted Crypt" horror maze continues from 7 to 10 p.m. at 
13662 Atlantis Way, Garden Grove. Admission: $1 to $2. Call (714) 641-9731. 
</P>
<P>
The fourth annual "Chamber of Horrors" haunted maze continues from 7 p.m. to 
midnight in the parking lot at Peppers restaurant, 12361 Chapman Ave., Garden 
Grove. Admission: $3.50 to $5.50. Call (714) 740-1333. 
</P>
<P>
The 18th annual Halloween Haunt continues from 7 p.m. to 1 a.m. at Knott's 
Berry Farm, 8039 Beach Blvd., Buena Park. Tickets: $25. Call (714) 827-1776. 
</P>
<P>
"Little Shop of Horrors" is being staged at 7 p.m. in the Mainstage Theatre at 
Golden West College, 15744 Golden West St., Huntington Beach. Tickets: $10. 
Call (714) 895-8378. 
</P>
<P>
"Seance" is being staged at 8 and 11 p.m. in the Drama Lab at Orange Coast 
College, 2701 Fairview Road, Costa Mesa. Tickets: $5. Call (714) 432-5880. 
</P>
<P>
Elektric Eyes plays rock during at a costume party beginning at 8 p.m. at 
Peppers Golden Bear, 300 Pacific Coast Highway, Huntington Beach. Admission: 
$10, includes food, dancing, entertainment and prizes. Call (714) 374-2327. 
</P>
<P>
The Cramm Brothers and Family Affair play rock at 8 p.m. during a costume party 
at the Coach House, 33157 Camino Capistrano, San Juan Capistrano. Admission: 
$10, includes prizes for best costumes. Call (714) 496-8930. 
</P>
<P>
Fun House presents its annual Halloween Bash at 8 p.m. at Old World, 7561 
Center Ave., Huntington Beach. Admission: $10, includes a special effects maze, 
games, prizes, dancing and more. Tickets: $10. Call (213) 430-8426. 
</P>
<P>
Touch of Country plays at 8 p.m. during a Halloween hoedown at the Crazy Horse 
Steak House, 1580 Brookhollow Drive, Santa Ana. Admission: free. Call (714) 
549-1512. 
</P>
<P>
Johnny Monster &amp; the Nightmares, Medicine Rattle and Heat &amp; Dust play 
rock at 9 p.m. at NYC, 17th Street and Newport Boulevard, Costa Mesa. 
Admission: $6. Call (714) 645-7313. 
</P>
<P>
The Pocket Rockets play blues during a costume party beginning at 9 p.m. at 
Cafe Lido, 501 30th St., Newport Beach. Admission: $5. Call (714) 675-2968. 
</P>
<P>
"Countess Dracula" is being staged at 9 p.m. at the Way Off Broadway Playhouse, 
1058 E. 1st St., Santa Ana. Tickets: $12. Call (714) 547-8997. Review, this 
page. 
</P>
<P>
A special Halloween screening of "Rocky Horror Picture Show" begins at 11 p.m. 
at the Balboa Theatre, 709 E. Balboa Blvd., Newport Beach. Admission: $6. 
Admission: $6. Call (714) 675-3570. 
</P>
</TEXT>
