<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: BANKING/ FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by James S. Granelli Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hands-On Help: More people in Orange County try to start new ventures than 
entrepreneurs anywhere else, says Tiffany A. Haugen at UC Irvine's Graduate 
School of Management. 
</P>
<P>
Part of the reason is that venture capital firms and other professionals have 
flocked to the county and helped to build a foundation that finances and 
supports entrepreneurs. 
</P>
<P>
But UCI has found that more is needed, and Haugen has come up with a program 
called Accelerate. The educational program provides hands-on help to new 
business executives who are trying to develop plans, finance their operations 
and expand from a start-up shop to companies with $50 million in sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
