<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 MORE SUSPECTS JAILED IN KILLING OF SEAMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two more suspected gang members were arrested Tuesday, bringing to four the 
number of suspects jailed in the shooting death of a Navy seaman who challenged 
graffiti-writing gang members, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Alexander Albert Jacinto, 20, and a 16-year-old boy whose name was withheld, 
were booked on suspicion of murder at the Carson sheriff's station about 11:30 
a.m. Tuesday, Deputy Rafael Estrada said. 
</P>
<P>
Their hometowns were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
Real Sabio Tojot, 19, and Ronald Caasi Caampued, 18, both of Carson, were 
arrested Monday on suspicion of murder and also held without bail. A 
.38-caliber pistol believed to be the murder weapon was confiscated. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, Alfred Kuhia Jr., 21, of Buena Park was a seaman aboard the USS 
Fort Fisher based in San Diego. He and two friends saw about a dozen gang 
members painting slogans on a wall in Carson Friday. When Kuhia told them to 
stop, one gang member shot him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
