<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MURDER CHARGE FILED IN NURSE'S STABBING 
DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A murder charge that carries a possible death sentence was filed Tuesday 
against a construction worker accused of fatally stabbing an emergency-room 
nurse in her Beverlywood home. 
</P>
<P>
Jose Francisco Guerra, 31, was awaiting arraignment in West Los Angeles 
Municipal Court. The district attorney's office charged him with a single 
murder count plus a special-circumstance allegation -- lying in wait -- that 
would qualify him for a possible death sentence if convicted. 
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors said Guerra fatally stabbed Kathleen Powell, a nurse at the Beverly 
Hills Medical Center, in her house last Thursday. Guerra, who was doing 
renovation work on the house next to Powell's, was arrested Friday. 
</P>
