<P>
BLAST DESTROYS SECURITY BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VACAVILLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An explosion ripped through a branch of the Security Pacific Bank today, 
triggering a fire that destroyed the building. 
</P>
<P>
Fire officials were on the scene this morning trying to determine the cause of 
the 1 a.m. blast, which they said may have resulted from a bomb or a gas main. 
</P>
<P>
"It was definitely an explosion," said acting Capt. Joel Brick. "It was heard 
by numerous neighbors. Parts of the building are in the front of the street. 
The building was . . . destroyed by fire and a good part of the front of the 
building was blown off, that's what it looks like." 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported, and an estimate of damages wasn't immediately 
available. 
</P>
</TEXT>
