<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
'65 TWINS TO FACE DODGERS IN FEB. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHOENIX 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 1965 Minnesota Twins, who lost the World Series in seven games to Los 
Angeles, will get another shot at the Dodgers in the 1991 Dream Game. 
</P>
<P>
The seven-inning benefit game will be played Feb. 3 at Phoenix Municipal 
Stadium, with proceeds going to the child development center at Phoenix 
Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The game has matched noteworthy teams of the past in a series that began in 
1986. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm glad to play for two reasons," former Twins ace Jim (Mudcat) Grant, now a 
Los Angeles businessman, said. "It's for a good cause, and it gives Minnesota 
another chance to get even with those suckers." 
</P>
<P>
Sandy Koufax, pitching on two day's rest, beat the Twins 2-0 in Game 7 to give 
Los Angeles the title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
