<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
TYSON ASSAULT CASE GOES TO JURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Mike Tyson assault case went to the jury today after the fighter's attorney 
accused the woman who sued of concocting the allegations as a way to get rich 
quick. 
</P>
<P>
Her lawyer, however, urged jurors in closing arguments to believe her version 
of events because she had the "courage and guts" to take on the former world 
heavyweight champion. 
</P>
<P>
Sandra Miller, a 26-year-old computer operator from Queens, claims that Tyson 
grabbed her buttocks and breasts, cursed at her and threatened to punch her 
after she refused his advances at a Manhattan dance club Dec. 10, 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Tyson, who testified during the three-day trial, acknowledges that he was at 
Bentley's Disco that night but denies knowing or ever touching Miller. 
</P>
<P>
Miller is seeking up to $3.5 million in civil damages for assault and battery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
